<!--
    Japanese (ja) — translated from values-de/ (German source of truth).

    Script notes:
    • Kanji, Hiragana, and Katakana are all used here as appropriate.
    • Katakana is used for loan words (e.g. バックアップ, バイオメトリクス).
    • Units are written with the standard Japanese half-width numerals and
      abbreviated forms (ml → ml, g → g, % → %).
    • The Japanese convention for time uses 時 (ji) for hour and 分 (fun) for
      minute; "17:00" is kept as-is since the app uses 24-hour clock display.
    • The polite (丁寧語) register is used throughout for UI strings.
    • "Binge drinking" is rendered as 過度飲酒 (kado inshu) — the established
      Japanese public-health term.
    • DHS (Deutsche Hauptstelle für Suchtfragen) is kept as "DHS" since no
      Japanese equivalent exists; WHO is written WHO (standard global usage).
    • day_change_time_value: Japanese omits "Uhr"; time stands alone as HH:MM.
-->
